<FIRST>u w AM-InfantTossed     10-20 0243</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Infant Tossed,240</SECOND>
<HEAD>Mother Throws 3-Week-Old Baby From Third-Floor Window</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 3-week-old girl survived being thrown out of
a third-floor window by her mother Friday when she landed in mud
left by days of steady rain, authorities said.
   ``She has a skull fracture, she appears to have a femur fracture
and we're concerned about intra-abdominal injuries,'' Dr. Bruce
Klein said. ``I think she is a very, very lucky baby.''
   Salonda Ray originally was listed in critical condition at
Children's National Medical Center, but her condition was later
upgraded to serious.
   The child's mother, Mary Ray, 22, was led out of the apartment
complex smiling and talking to herself as neighbors jeered. As she
was placed in a police squad car, she turned toward television
cameras and said ``My, I feel good.'' She was to be arraigned in
D.C. Superior Court Saturday on charges of assault with intent to
kill, officials said.
   ``She has not indicated why'' she threw the infant out of the
window, Capt. William Ritchie, a spokesman of the district police
department said. ``But we believe that she has some very strong
religious beliefs. We are still in the process of investigating
that particular aspect.''
   A security guard at the apartment complex initially thought the
baby had been killed in the fall and put a coat over the body. The
little girl was rushed to the hospital after a neighbor lifted the
coat and the baby cried.
</TEXT>
