<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--DogShootsMan     10-20 0130</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Dog Shoots Man,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Spaniel Wings Master with Shotgun</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MAYVILLE, Wis. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hunting dog was so excited after
retrieving a pheasant that it danced into a shotgun trigger, and
the blast injured the dog's master.
   Christian Dobberpuhl, who had to have shotgun pellets removed
from his foot, doesn't bear his pet any ill-will.
   ``The dog is a good dog,'' Dobberpuhl said Friday.
   Dobberpuhl and a friend, Frank Coch, bagged two birds during the
expedition near Mayville, northwest of Milwaukee on Wednesday.
After returning with the second bird, the dog triggered a 12-gauge
shotgun lying on the ground, Dobberpuhl said.
   The noise ``didn't bother the dog at all,'' said Dobberpuhl, 77.
   ``It's a funny thing, you know: `Dog attacks man.' But it was a
freak accident,'' Dobberpuhl said.
</TEXT>
