<FIRST>r a BC-Quotes     10-20 0182</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Quotes,0186</SECOND>
<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``It kills you. It just kills you. We all have families, you
know. ... The adults are no problem. But the kids ... '' _ Oakland,
Calif., firefighter Lee Kraft, dabbing tears, after he pulled the
bodies of a 6-year-old girl and her mother out of the Nimitz
Freeway, part of which collapsed the earthquake.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``I can't stop shaking ... I guess I'm surviving, but I'm
scared.'' _ Marcelina Toussaint, 73, of Watsonville, Calif., a town
near the epicenter of the magnitude 6.9 quake and wracked by four
strong aftershocks.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``We face no sudden or uncontrollable burst of flag destruction
... Yet we are being asked to believe that the flag which neither
Hitler nor Stalin could defeat is now threatened by a single
misguided person who most Americans never heard of and don't care
about.'' _ Senate Majority Leader George J. Mitchell, referring to
Texas flag-burner Gregory Lee Johnson, whose conviction the Supreme
Court overturned on free-speech grounds, before the Senate defeated
a proposed constitutional amendment to ban flag burning.
</TEXT>
