<FILEID>AP-NR-10-20-89 0319EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>u a AM-SFQuake-Wreck 1stLd-Writethru a0467 10-20 0198</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-SF Quake-Wreck, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0467,0198</SECOND>
<HEAD>Truck Goes Over Edge of Freeway Destroyed by Quake</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS throughout to UPDATE with driver member of crew inspecting
interstate, serious injuries, fixes that driver drove off highway, sted
of crashing through barrier; no pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An upset member of a crew inspecting the
crumpled Interstate 880 drove a truck off the edge of the highway
late Thursday, officials said. The truck fell 30 feet.
   The driver was taken to Highland Hospital in Oakland, officials
said. No condition was immediately available, but a police officer
said the driver had serious injuries.
   The crew member worked for the California Department of
Transportation, and was working near the section of freeway that
buckled and trapped an undetermined number of drivers inside in
Tuesday's earthquake, according to Lisa Murphy, a department
spokeswoman. The quake registered a 6.9 on the Richter scale.
   The driver was ``upset over something, but I don't know what,''
said Sgt. John Silva. He said the driver expressed anger to the
last person he spoke with before he left the scene.
   The accident occurred at 10:30 p.m. at the northern end of the
twisted section of freeway.
</TEXT>
