<HEAD>Truck Goes Over Edge of Crumpled I-880</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A member of a crew inspecting a collapsed
section of Interstate 880 apparently became confused when leaving
the site and drove a truck off the edge of the highway, officials
said. The truck fell 30 feet.
   Lawrence Benigno, who works for the California Department of
Transportation, was pried from the truck Thursday night and taken
to Highland Hospital, according to Lisa Murphy, a department
spokeswoman.
