Patrol Sgt. John Silva said Benigno suffered cuts and bruises, and
possibly a fractured hand.
   Silva said earlier that Benigno was upset shortly before the
accident. But he said a witness who gave him that information was
mistaken. Silva said Benigno was working at the site for the first
time and became confused as he drove off.
   The accident occurred at about 10:30 p.m. at the northern end of
the twisted section of freeway that crumpled in Tuesday's quake and
trapped an undetermined number of drivers inside.
