<HEAD>Burma Sentences 100 to Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RANGOON, Burma (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Civilian courts and military tribunals
have sentenced 100 people to death during the past three months,
the government announced today.
   Col. Aung Thein, a government spokesman, told a news conference
that of the 100 sentences, 24 were passed by military courts set up
to deal with ``serious offenses.''
   How many, if any, among the 100 have been executed was not
announced. Neither were the alleged crimes of those condemned to
