was ``based out'' on co`his eyes looked like they
were going to jump ocaine and that `ut of his head'' during the confrontation.
   Harvie Eugene Duckett, 30, pleaded guilty to being an accessory
in connection with the case and was expected to testify against
Bridges.
   Bridges has had several other brushes with the law. He pleaded
no contest last year to charges he made bomb threats against an
auto customizer he hired to work on a car of his. Also last year,
he was convicted of reckless driving, and in 1983 he paid a $240
