<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--GenerousRobber     10-20 0170</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Generous Robber,0175</SECOND>
<HEAD>Robber `Tips' Victim</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DULUTH, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A security systems owner says he was robbed
at knifepoint by a woman who took about $200, but gave him $20 back
and thanked him for being ``most generous.''
   ``I got a tip for being robbed,'' Charles Grubb said Thursday.
   ``She confronted me with a meat-carving knife,'' said Grubb, 50,
who was returning to his car after dinner in downtown Duluth
Wednesday. ``It looked like a machete. She was extremely nervous.
She told me, `I've used this before, and I wouldn't hesitate to use
it again.'''
   After taking the money and giving some of it back, the woman ran
down an alley, Grubb said.
   A few hours later, police arrested a 24-year-old woman staying
at the downtown YWCA and took her to St. Luke's Hospital for
psychiatric observation. Charges were pending.
   Grubb, who sells security systems for homes and businesses, said
he'll use his experience in his sales pitch.
   ``The message is,'' he said, ``it can happen to anyone.''
</TEXT>
