<HEAD>`Dangerous Games,' A Musical, to Close</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``Dangerous Games,'' a tango musical created by
director and choreographer Graciela Daniele, is the first flop of
the fall Broadway season.
   The show, which opened Thursday to negative reviews, closes
Saturday after four performances and 12 previews, said Robert
Larkin, its press representative.
   ``Dangerous Games'' is the collective title for the musical's
two acts. The first, called ``Tango,'' takes place in a bordello,
and the second, ``Orfeo,'' is a retelling of the Orpheus legend.
   Wrote Frank Rich in The New York Times, ``She (Daniele) has
slammed together two hours of mediocre Broadway routines padded by
repetition and crushed by pretense.''
</TEXT>
