   Tass added that a group of volunteer rescuers who gained
experience in the aftermath of the earthquake that devastated
northern Armenia in December are also prepared to fly to California.
   Millions of dollars in aid and thousands of foreign rescuers and
doctors poured into Armenia after the Dec. 7 earthquake, which left
25,000 dead.
