<FIRST>r a AM-FiestyFeline     10-20 0221</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Fiesty Feline,0227</SECOND>
<HEAD>Courageous Calico Saves Poodle From Pit Bull</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DORA, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A courageous calico cat took a flying leap and
sent a pit bull dog running when it tried to beat up a poodle.
   Teresa Harper's 4-year-old feline, named Sparky, became a local
hero after saving her owner's poodle named Lacy Jane from the jaws
of the pit bull.
   ``I feel she's definitely a hero,'' said Mrs. Harper. ``My
poodle would be dead otherwise.''
   Mrs. Harper said she let her dog out this week and seconds later
heard a commotion. She rushed to the door and was paralyzed with
fear when she saw Lacy Jane being attacked by a stray pit bull.
   But Sparky, perched 10 feet above the fray, flew into action.
   ``She made a flying leap, just as pretty as you please, and she
landed right on that dog's head,'' her owner said. ``She just
clawed and scratched and clawed and scratched.''
   The pit bull ran off to take cover. Mrs. Harper snatched the
wounded Lacy Jane, blood flowing from a gash in her neck and raced
to a veterinarian.
   ``The poodle had a puncture wound on the right side,'' said
Vicky Moorehead, a Sumiton Animal Clinic employee. ``It would have
been killed if it hadn't have been for that cat. This is just
amazing.''
</TEXT>
