<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Angola-Crash     10-20 0074</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Angola-Crash,0076</SECOND>
<HEAD>Helicopter Crashes, Killing Four</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LUANDA, Angola (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Soviet-built military helicopter crashed
in northern Angola, killing four people on board and seriously
injuring a fifth, a government statement said Friday.
   According to the statement from the defense ministry, the MI-35
helicopter crashed near Macocolo, about 300 miles northeast of
Luanda in Uige province, which borders Zaire.
   The statement said the crash occurred in bad weather but gave no
further details.
</TEXT>
