<FILEID>AP-NR-10-20-89 2142EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i AM-Italy-Quake     10-20 0166</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Italy-Quake,0170</SECOND>
<HEAD>Quake Shakes Hills Outside Rome, No Injuries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An early morning quake shook the hill country south
of Rome, creating panic and minor structural damage to buildings
but authorities said no injuries were reported.
   Local police and fire departments said hundreds of residents of
the Alban Hills called in to say they were frightened by the
temblor, which lasted about 10 seconds.
   ``The San Francisco effect and the fact it happened during the
night caused the worry,'' the Italian news agency ANSA quoted an
official of the Civil Defense Ministry as saying, referring to the
quake that struck the Bay area this week.
   The temblor, which shook an area about 15 miles south of Rome,
registered 6 to 7 on the 12-point Mercalli scale. An earthquake of
that magnitude can cause serious damage. The Mercalli and Richter
scales are not convertible.
   Firemen said the walls of hospitals in Rocca di Papa and Albano
sustained minor cracks but no major structural damage.
</TEXT>
