<FIRST>r a AM-DouglasDispatchSale     10-20 0196</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Douglas Dispatch Sale,0200</SECOND>
<HEAD>Wick Communications Announces Nov. 1 Acquisition of Douglas Dispatch</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SIERRA VISTA, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wick Communications on Friday
announced it will purchase the Douglas Daily Dispatch from Western
Newspapers effective Nov. 1.
   Neither Sierra Vista-based Wick Communications nor Yuma-based
Western Newspapers disclosed the purchase price.
   Wick Communications, owned by brothers Walter and Robert Wick,
already owns 25 daily and weekly newspapers, including the other
two daily newspapers in southeastern Arizona's Cochise County: the
Sierra Vista Herald and the Bisbee Daily Review. Each publishes six
days a week. The Dispatch publishes five days a week.
   The Wicks said Greg LaFreniere would be the Dispatch's new
publisher. LaFreniere, 48, is the publisher of Wick Communication
weeklies in the Cochise County communities of Willcox and Benson.
He will continue as publisher of those two newspapers in addition
to his new duties.
   Western Newspapers purchased the Dispatch in March 1985 from
Thomson Newspapers.
   Don Soldwedel, Western Newspapers chairman, said the Dispatch's
current publisher, Robin Richards, will be transferred to another
Western Newspapers property.
   Western owns daily and weekly newspapers, a commercial printing
company and an outdoor advertising company, with operations in
Arizona, California and Nevada.
</TEXT>
