<HEAD>Gunmen Kill One Policeman, Injure Another in Ambush</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: To DELETE extraneous word, SUB 3rd graf: `The incident...IRA
stronghold.' Pickup last graf, `The mainly...'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELFAST, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gunman killed one policeman and
injured another when they ambushed the officers' car in a southern
community Friday night, police said.
   No group immediately claimed responsibility but suspicion fell
on the Irish Republican Army, which is fighting British rule in
Northern Ireland.
   Police did not immediately release the names of the police
officers involved.
   The incident occurred in South Armagh, an IRA stronghold.
   The mainly Roman Catholic IRA wants to unite predominantly
Protestant Northern Ireland with the Republic of Ireland under
socialist rule. The republic is overwhelmingly Catholic.
