<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Apple     10-20 0180</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Apple,0187</SECOND>
<HEAD>Apple Earnings Rise 49 Percent, Helped By Special Item</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Apple Computer Inc.'s earnings rose 49 percent
in the latest quarter, mainly because of a gain from the sale of
its stock in Adobe Systems Inc., the company said Friday.
   Operating income before the Adobe gain and taxes and interest
rose a narrower 2 percent.
   Apple Chairman John Sculley said the company was recovering from
a squeeze on profit margins caused by high component costs. Apple
was faulted for buying large quantities of computer chips at
unusually high prices during a temporary shortage last year.
   Earnings in Apple's fourth quarter rose to $161.1 million, or
$1.24 a share, including an after-tax gain of $48 million from the
Adobe sale. That was up from $107.9 million, or 84 cents a share, a
year earlier. Revenue rose to $1.38 billion from $1.17 billion.
   For the full fiscal year, Apple's earnings rose to $454 million,
or $3.53 a share, from $400.3 million, or $3.08 a share, a year
earlier. Revenue rose to $5.28 billion from $4.07 billion.
</TEXT>
