<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-MediaGeneral     10-20 0157</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Media General,0163</SECOND>
<HEAD>Media General Reports Third-Quarter Profit Decline</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RICHMOND (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Media General Inc. said Friday its profit fell
about 63 percent in the latest quarter, attributing the decline to
weakness in newspaper advvertising linage and declines in newsprint
sales.
   Profit fell to $3.94 million, or 15 cents a share, from $10.8
million, or 38 cents a share, a year earlier. Revenue fell to
$142.3 million from $181.8 million during the same period last
year, the company said.
   During the first nine months of 1989, profit fell to $21.9
million, or 84 cents a share, from $38.4 million, or $1.34 a share,
a year earlier. Revenue totaled $441.5 million, compared with
$564.4 million the year before.
   The company said the sale last year of the broadcast services
unit and a newsprint mill in Pomona, Calif., account for the
decline in revenues.
   The company said there was encouraging growth in net paid
circulation of its newspapers.
</TEXT>
